extraembryonic mesoderm","Extraembryonic mesoderm core surrounded by syncytiotrophoblast","Syncytiotrophoblast core surrounded by cytotrophoblast","Cytotrophoblast core surrounded by syncytiotrophoblast","Extraembryonic mesoderm core surrounded by cytotrophoblast"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EPrimary chorionic villi form around day 13 post-fertilisation and consist of a \u003Cstrong\u003Ecytotrophoblast core surrounded by syncytiotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E. This arrangement is essential for early placental development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect arrangements can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESyncytiotrophoblast core surrounded by extraembryonic mesoderm\u003C/strong\u003E - This arrangement does not occur during placental development\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtraembryonic mesoderm core surrounded by syncytiotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes a later stage (secondary villus)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESyncytiotrophoblast core surrounded by cytotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the reverse of the correct arrangement\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExtraembryonic mesoderm core surrounded by cytotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes a variant of secondary villus structure\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPrimary villi later develop into secondary villi when extraembryonic mesoderm invades the cytotrophoblast core. These then become tertiary villi when blood vessels develop within the mesoderm, forming the functional units of the mature placenta.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Primary chorionic villi consist of a cytotrophoblast core surrounded by syncytiotrophoblast","Primary chorionic villi form during early placental development around day 13 post-fertilisation","Primary villi develop into secondary villi when invaded by extraembryonic mesoderm, and later into tertiary villi when blood vessels form"],"references":["Kojima J, Ono M, Kuji N, Nishi H. Human Chorionic Villous Differentiation and Placental Development. Int J Mol Sci. 2022 Jul 20;23(14):8003. doi: 10.3390/ijms23148003. PMID: 35887349; PMCID: PMC9325306.","Jones TM, Montero FJ. Chorionic Villus Sampling. [Updated 2022 Dec 11]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK563301/","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences.","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57520"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15887"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57520","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57520"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T21:45:25+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T21:50:30+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8578"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72050"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app